<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3378] c_glib service does not handle negative Thrift byte values correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3378</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a problematic type cast in generated c_glib service code that treat the sign bit of gint8 as normal bit (i.e. 128).&lt;br/&gt;
The problem is illustrated as follows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i = 0;
users_handler_func((*gint8)&amp;amp;i);  &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// Suppose &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; function tries to set i to -100
&lt;/span&gt;store_handler_result(i);         &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// This stores 156, not -100&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
